{
  "texts": [
    "Photogrammetry needs a conventional camera to capture the images, a computer, and specialized software to create the 3D representation of the objects.",
    "Photogrammetry, the same as laser scanning, can be terrestrial, based on photos taken from the ground, or aerial, based on photos taken from an aerial vehicle with a mounted camera.The most common aerial vehicles for point cloud capturing, are the Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs), namely drones.",
    "A UAV is an aircraft without a pilot that has an assistive onboard system that is controlled remotely or autonomously [70].",
    "Various categories of drones differ in terms of flexibility, accuracy, weight, and performance in altering weather conditions.",
    "A general categorization is to classify them according to their flight mechanism into Multi-Rotor Fixed-Wing and Hybrid-Wing drones [71]."
  ]
}